text: The spinybottom tree frog, Tramlap flying tree frog, or Tay Nguyen flying tree frog (Rhacophorus exechopygus) is a frog. It lives in Vietnam and in the Annamite Mountains in Laos, between 800 and 1400 meters above sea level. Scientists think it could also live in Cambodia. ==References== Category:Frogs of Asia
title: Rhacophorus exechopygus
